h3. Issue Summary

When create or edit an Epic issue Type, there are a word and a message in English, when using JIRA in French Language:

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Open an Epic issue type
# Click on “Edit”
h3. Expected Results

{code:java}
“Lien épique”
{code}

{code:java}
“Choisissez une épopée à laquelle attribuer ce problème.“{code}

h3. Actual Results

 * The Field name is in English:
{code:java}
“Epic Link”{code}

 * The message is in English:
{code:java}
“Choose an epic to assign this issue to.“{code}

h3. Workaround

 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
When commenting on an issue and change to Activity tab, there are some words with wrong spelling when JIRA is in French Language:
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Open an issue
 # Write a comment
 # Click on “Activity” to see the comment just created
h3. Expected Results
{code:java}
“Aujourd’hui”{code}
{code:java}
“À l’instant”{code}
h3. Actual Results
 * There is a spelling mistake in “Aujourd”hui”, a double apostrophe *“*:
{code:java}
“Aujourd’’hui”{code}
 * There is a spelling mistake in “À linstant”, missing apostrophe after *l*:
{code:java}
“Aujourd’hui”{code}

h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

After investigation in the case:
 [https://getsupport.atlassian.com/browse/JST-524245]

we found that translation key causes a problem:
{noformat}
"gadget.activity.stream.config.numofentries":"Ограничить <span classgadget.activity.stream.config.option.name={0}"{noformat}

 In en-us:
{noformat}
"gadget.activity.stream.config.numofentries": "Limit to <span class="input-container"></span> items"{noformat}

It looks like a combination of two fields. The html tags are required for this component to work.
